1
00:00:00,083 --> 00:00:02,336
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:22,583 --> 00:01:28,505
LOVE

3
00:01:28,589 --> 00:01:29,548
YAGAMI

4
00:01:29,673 --> 00:01:31,174
[Soichiro] Light, Ryuzaki has decided

5
00:01:31,258 --> 00:01:33,385
that he'd like you to help
with the investigation.

6
00:01:33,468 --> 00:01:36,013
If you're still interested, then you need
to come here right away.

7
00:01:36,597 --> 00:01:38,265
-[Light] Okay, Dad.
-[Ryuk crunching]

8
00:01:40,183 --> 00:01:43,687
All along I've been trying to find a way
to get involved in the investigation.

9
00:01:44,062 --> 00:01:46,356
But I never thought
they would actually approach me.

10
00:01:46,565 --> 00:01:49,651
Now I'll have access
to classified information about the case,

11
00:01:49,818 --> 00:01:52,654
which means I can learn more
about this other Kira.

12
00:01:52,904 --> 00:01:55,365
I need to figure out
what this impostor is all about

13
00:01:55,490 --> 00:01:57,951
before someone else
on the Task Force beats me to it.

14
00:01:59,911 --> 00:02:02,289
-[L] Thank you, Light.
-Not at all.

15
00:02:02,581 --> 00:02:05,626
After all, I want to catch Kira
as much as you do, Ryuga.

16
00:02:06,001 --> 00:02:08,128
I'll have to ask that you call me
"Ryuzaki" here.

17
00:02:08,253 --> 00:02:08,879
Huh?

18
00:02:09,212 --> 00:02:10,297
I'm Matsui.

19
00:02:10,380 --> 00:02:11,381
I'm Aihara.

20
00:02:11,590 --> 00:02:12,924
And I'm Asahi.

21
00:02:14,259 --> 00:02:15,385
Yes, of course.

22
00:02:15,761 --> 00:02:18,472
Then, perhaps I should call myself
"Light Asahi?"

23
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:20,015
[L] Yes, please do.

24
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:23,352
To keep things simple from this point on,
I'll call you "Light."

25
00:02:24,102 --> 00:02:25,562
Okay, let's get down to work.

26
00:02:25,854 --> 00:02:28,649
You can start by looking over
all the information we've collected.

27
00:02:28,732 --> 00:02:30,525
I'd also like you to examine these videos.

28
00:02:31,109 --> 00:02:33,695
They were sent to the TV station
but were never aired.

29
00:02:34,071 --> 00:02:36,406
For security reasons,
you're not permitted to take notes,

30
00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:38,367
and all materials must remain here.

31
00:02:38,492 --> 00:02:39,368
I understand.

32
00:02:39,826 --> 00:02:41,161
We will begin now.

33
00:02:41,662 --> 00:02:42,829
[beeping]

34
00:02:44,581 --> 00:02:45,749
Light...

35
00:02:47,709 --> 00:02:49,252
THE PREVIOUS NIGHT

36
00:02:49,461 --> 00:02:52,047
Well then, we need to ask Light Yagami
to assist us.

37
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:55,092
However, we cannot tell him
that we're considering the possibility

38
00:02:55,175 --> 00:02:56,468
of a second Kira.

39
00:02:56,593 --> 00:03:00,013
Are you serious? But wouldn't that make
working together a bit difficult?

40
00:03:00,389 --> 00:03:03,892
He's right. Why even bother asking him
to work with us?

41
00:03:04,059 --> 00:03:05,852
[L] Well, I didn't mean indefinitely.

42
00:03:06,061 --> 00:03:08,522
I'm curious to see what his impression
of these tapes will be

43
00:03:08,605 --> 00:03:09,564
prior to knowing ours.

44
00:03:09,648 --> 00:03:10,524
COPY 1

45
00:03:10,691 --> 00:03:13,568
Light's deductive reasoning
is really quite incredible.

46
00:03:13,735 --> 00:03:16,947
He may suspect that these tapes
are the work of a second Kira,

47
00:03:17,030 --> 00:03:19,366
an impostor or copycat
imitating the original.

48
00:03:19,908 --> 00:03:21,702
But the basis for the second Kira theory

49
00:03:21,785 --> 00:03:23,537
is that the victims
of these recent killings

50
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:26,081
were minor criminals who don't fit
the normal profile.

51
00:03:26,248 --> 00:03:29,084
Without hearing our explanation,
how will Light ever know that?

52
00:03:29,292 --> 00:03:31,169
[L] Yes, but there's more to it than that.

53
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:33,880
The suspect that we've been pursuing
up until now

54
00:03:33,964 --> 00:03:37,426
has needed both a name and a face
to kill his victims.

55
00:03:37,634 --> 00:03:39,845
But there's something different
happening here.

56
00:03:40,011 --> 00:03:43,390
Recall that Mr. Ukita was killed
the moment he arrived at the station,

57
00:03:44,641 --> 00:03:46,810
and this Kira demanded only
that I appear on TV

58
00:03:46,977 --> 00:03:48,770
but made no request for my name.

59
00:03:49,146 --> 00:03:51,064
This implies that the second Kira

60
00:03:51,148 --> 00:03:53,400
only needs to see a person's face
to kill them.

61
00:03:54,359 --> 00:03:56,778
So, I'll ask Light to look over
all of our information

62
00:03:56,862 --> 00:03:58,321
as well as our video evidence.

63
00:03:58,405 --> 00:04:01,408
If he comes to the conclusion
that there could be a second suspect

64
00:04:01,491 --> 00:04:04,453
then he'd be almost completely cleared
of suspicion in this case.

65
00:04:04,578 --> 00:04:06,329
[Soichiro]
But how will that prove anything?

66
00:04:07,205 --> 00:04:09,875
Logically, if he's really Kira,
he'll want me dead,

67
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:12,836
seeing as I'm the one leading
the investigation against him right now.

68
00:04:13,086 --> 00:04:14,421
And the ways things are going,

69
00:04:14,546 --> 00:04:16,506
if I comply
with this new subject's demands

70
00:04:16,631 --> 00:04:20,051
and appear on TV in three days,
there's a very good chance I will die.

71
00:04:20,844 --> 00:04:25,348
I can't see the real Kira jeopardizing
such an easy opportunity to get rid of me.

72
00:04:25,432 --> 00:04:26,725
Okay, but are you suggesting

73
00:04:26,808 --> 00:04:29,269
that if my son does not come
to the same conclusion,

74
00:04:29,352 --> 00:04:31,229
there's an even greater chance
that he is guilty?

75
00:04:31,563 --> 00:04:35,233
No. In that case, there will still only be
a five-percent chance.

76
00:04:35,525 --> 00:04:38,612
We'll inform him that we are investigating
the possibility of a copycat

77
00:04:38,695 --> 00:04:41,323
and have him cooperate with us as planned.

78
00:04:41,907 --> 00:04:43,074
[sighs]

79
00:04:45,202 --> 00:04:47,245
[Kira] Now that you've seen
proof of my powers,

80
00:04:47,412 --> 00:04:49,956
you should have no trouble
believing that I am Kira.

81
00:04:50,415 --> 00:04:53,335
-On the designated...
-[Light] This video is so mediocre,

82
00:04:53,543 --> 00:04:55,170
it's making me sick to my stomach.

83
00:04:55,253 --> 00:04:57,547
I don't know,
maybe it's because I'm the real one.

84
00:04:57,714 --> 00:05:01,384
But this is a complete disgrace
to everything Kira stands for.

85
00:05:02,886 --> 00:05:04,262
Something's not right here.

86
00:05:04,888 --> 00:05:07,557
Seems unusual that no one bothered
to explain this video to me.

87
00:05:08,058 --> 00:05:09,226
It's not like them.

88
00:05:09,559 --> 00:05:12,395
Well, in any case,
I'd be stupid to comment on it.

89
00:05:12,604 --> 00:05:14,356
It's probably best if I say nothing.

90
00:05:14,481 --> 00:05:17,150
If I just leave it alone, L dies.

91
00:05:17,734 --> 00:05:19,444
So, what do you make of this, Light?

92
00:05:19,528 --> 00:05:21,363
Have you come to any conclusions?

93
00:05:21,446 --> 00:05:22,489
Hmm?

94
00:05:24,574 --> 00:05:26,243
Damn, it's a test!

95
00:05:27,202 --> 00:05:28,495
It's hard to say for sure

96
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:30,914
but there might be another person
out there with Kira's power.

97
00:05:31,248 --> 00:05:32,791
With Kira's power?

98
00:05:32,999 --> 00:05:34,709
But what do you mean by that, Light?

99
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:36,586
At the very least, I'd say this tape

100
00:05:36,670 --> 00:05:38,964
was not created by the Kira
we're familiar with.

101
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:41,508
It's extremely out of character for him

102
00:05:41,591 --> 00:05:43,802
to use these kinds of victims
for his killings.

103
00:05:44,427 --> 00:05:47,305
And since we've established
that he needs a name and face to kill,

104
00:05:47,389 --> 00:05:49,683
it makes you wonder how he was able
to kill that detective

105
00:05:49,766 --> 00:05:53,061
and those two officers right outside
the television station like that.

106
00:05:53,979 --> 00:05:55,605
It's the same.

107
00:05:55,772 --> 00:05:59,359
That's almost exactly how L...
I mean, Ryuzaki said it.

108
00:05:59,776 --> 00:06:01,486
That was incredible, Light.

109
00:06:01,611 --> 00:06:04,114
Now, any doubts about you
should be resolved.

110
00:06:05,115 --> 00:06:07,075
I think you're exactly right about that.

111
00:06:07,492 --> 00:06:10,370
We also believe that this is the work
of a second Kira.

112
00:06:10,704 --> 00:06:11,788
[Light] I knew it.

113
00:06:12,497 --> 00:06:15,834
So you knew about this all along, Ryuga...
Sorry, Ryuzaki?

114
00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:18,712
Which means this was
just another one of your tests?

115
00:06:18,837 --> 00:06:20,672
It wasn't my intention to test you.

116
00:06:21,006 --> 00:06:24,175
The truth is, if I was the only one
who thought there was a second Kira,

117
00:06:24,259 --> 00:06:25,552
it wouldn't be too convincing.

118
00:06:26,094 --> 00:06:28,430
But the fact that we both came
to the same conclusion

119
00:06:28,513 --> 00:06:30,515
makes the theory
that much more believable.

120
00:06:30,974 --> 00:06:33,143
As expected, you did not disappoint us.

121
00:06:33,518 --> 00:06:34,728
You've been a great help.

122
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:36,730
It's decided then.

123
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:40,191
First, we must focus on stopping
this copycat.

124
00:06:40,525 --> 00:06:43,320
From what we've seen,
he sympathizes with the real Kira

125
00:06:43,403 --> 00:06:45,196
but clearly lacks his sophistication.

126
00:06:45,655 --> 00:06:48,366
I think he might even be willing
to obey the original.

127
00:06:49,159 --> 00:06:51,494
[L] If so, we could lure him into a trap

128
00:06:51,661 --> 00:06:54,205
by sending our own message
from the real Kira.

129
00:06:55,081 --> 00:06:56,708
I guess I shouldn't be surprised.

130
00:06:56,833 --> 00:06:59,210
You literally took the words
right out of my mouth.

131
00:07:00,503 --> 00:07:01,963
[L] Oh, and Light...

132
00:07:02,672 --> 00:07:04,925
I would like you to play the part
of the real Kira.

133
00:07:05,342 --> 00:07:07,469
Huh? Me as Kira?

134
00:07:07,761 --> 00:07:09,930
[L] Yes, you're the only one
I can think of

135
00:07:10,013 --> 00:07:11,806
who'd be able
to pull something like this off.

136
00:07:12,223 --> 00:07:14,392
At any rate, we don't have time to waste.

137
00:07:14,517 --> 00:07:16,811
Do you think you could script
a message from Kira

138
00:07:16,937 --> 00:07:19,689
in time for it to be aired
on this evening's national news?

139
00:07:19,814 --> 00:07:21,232
[Ryuk chuckles]

140
00:07:21,358 --> 00:07:22,275
[Light] Damn him.

141
00:07:22,651 --> 00:07:24,694
He must have been planning this
from the beginning.

142
00:07:24,778 --> 00:07:26,488
It's the only reason I'm here.

143
00:07:28,073 --> 00:07:30,116
[Light] Ryuzaki, does this look okay?

144
00:07:30,784 --> 00:07:32,535
I think I managed to make it believable.

145
00:07:34,746 --> 00:07:36,790
I think you've done
an excellent job with this.

146
00:07:37,248 --> 00:07:40,502
However, if we don't omit the part
that says, "You're free to kill L,"

147
00:07:40,752 --> 00:07:41,962
then I'm gonna end up dead.

148
00:07:42,212 --> 00:07:43,463
[chuckles]

149
00:07:43,964 --> 00:07:46,967
Uh, sorry. I guess I got carried away
playing the part.

150
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:50,261
I figured if I was him,
I'd probably demand that you be killed.

151
00:07:50,887 --> 00:07:52,347
I was improvising.

152
00:07:52,639 --> 00:07:54,683
Feel free to change it
to whatever you like.

153
00:07:54,808 --> 00:07:55,684
Sounds good.

154
00:07:57,435 --> 00:08:00,063
[L] Okay, Aihara, the script is ready.
I'll leave it to you.

155
00:08:00,313 --> 00:08:01,356
[Aihara] All right.

156
00:08:02,273 --> 00:08:04,109
And now, a shocking announcement.

157
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:08,863
In response to the frightening Kira video
aired on Sakura TV only a few days ago,

158
00:08:08,947 --> 00:08:12,325
an anonymous individual has contacted us
claiming to be the real Kira.

159
00:08:13,576 --> 00:08:17,038
In short, he has demanded of this network,
as well as several others,

160
00:08:17,122 --> 00:08:19,666
that we air the message
you are now about to see.

161
00:08:20,083 --> 00:08:22,127
I would also like to mention that the NPA

162
00:08:22,210 --> 00:08:24,129
has granted us permission
to air this video.

163
00:08:24,462 --> 00:08:27,340
Is this the real Kira?
No one knows for sure.

164
00:08:27,841 --> 00:08:30,010
But we can only hope this video
will provide us

165
00:08:30,093 --> 00:08:31,636
with some much-needed answers.

166
00:08:32,846 --> 00:08:33,930
[distorted voice] I am Kira.

167
00:08:34,305 --> 00:08:37,350
It worked! I knew he'd answer me.

168
00:08:37,434 --> 00:08:38,935
[distorted voice] The true Kira.

169
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:43,398
The one who was broadcast on Sakura TV
several days ago is a pretender.

170
00:08:43,565 --> 00:08:44,607
A fake.

171
00:08:44,733 --> 00:08:49,320
The purpose of this message is
to communicate my will to this impostor

172
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:52,073
I have chosen to be lenient with him
for the time being,

173
00:08:52,157 --> 00:08:54,659
only because I believe he wishes
to cooperate with me

174
00:08:54,868 --> 00:08:56,870
in the creation of a new world.

175
00:08:57,037 --> 00:08:59,164
But I want to make it absolutely clear

176
00:08:59,247 --> 00:09:02,167
that the taking of innocent lives
is against my will.

177
00:09:02,459 --> 00:09:05,628
If this person claiming to be me
is truly sympathetic to my cause

178
00:09:05,712 --> 00:09:08,548
and wishes to be of some help,
I ask two things of him:

179
00:09:08,631 --> 00:09:10,675
That he refrain from killing aimlessly

180
00:09:10,759 --> 00:09:12,886
and that he agree to abide
by my basic principles.

181
00:09:13,178 --> 00:09:15,930
[Misa] Yay! Now where is that camcorder?

182
00:09:16,681 --> 00:09:18,391
What are you planning to do?

183
00:09:18,475 --> 00:09:20,185
[Misa] Uh, hello!
Do you really need to ask?

184
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:22,145
I'm going to reply to him, of course.

185
00:09:22,645 --> 00:09:24,230
SEVERAL DAYS LATER

186
00:09:24,314 --> 00:09:26,399
[Watari] Ryuzaki, we have a reply
from the second Kira.

187
00:09:26,649 --> 00:09:28,401
-What?
-Really?

188
00:09:28,693 --> 00:09:31,821
I'll be bringing over the envelope
and tape that we received,

189
00:09:31,946 --> 00:09:35,867
but in the meantime, I'm streaming a copy
of the video so you can view on your end.

190
00:09:38,787 --> 00:09:40,789
[Second Kira]
Kira, thank you for your reply.

191
00:09:40,872 --> 00:09:41,956
Please do not worry.

192
00:09:42,040 --> 00:09:44,042
I will follow orders and do as you say.

193
00:09:44,584 --> 00:09:46,086
-Wow!
-It worked!

194
00:09:46,503 --> 00:09:48,630
[Light] "I will do as you say," huh?

195
00:09:48,797 --> 00:09:50,757
This guy's gonna be no help at all.

196
00:09:51,007 --> 00:09:53,676
If this fake had any idea
what my wishes were,

197
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:56,971
he'd insist that L appear on TV
and then kill him anyway.

198
00:09:57,388 --> 00:09:59,432
How could you fall
for something like this?

199
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:01,101
Damn it!

200
00:10:02,143 --> 00:10:03,895
[Second Kira] I really want to meet you.

201
00:10:05,271 --> 00:10:07,357
-I don't think you have the eyes.
-[Light gasps]

202
00:10:07,482 --> 00:10:10,151
[Second Kira] You don't have to worry.
I would never try to kill you.

203
00:10:10,652 --> 00:10:11,861
That's a promise.

204
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:14,114
[Light] What the hell is he thinking?

205
00:10:14,197 --> 00:10:17,492
Talking about Shinigami eyes
in a public message like this?

206
00:10:18,576 --> 00:10:20,954
What's this "having the eyes"
supposed to mean?

207
00:10:21,079 --> 00:10:22,622
-Is it a code?
-[L] Yeah.

208
00:10:23,414 --> 00:10:25,458
[Second Kira]
Please tell me how I can meet you

209
00:10:25,542 --> 00:10:26,626
without the police knowing.

210
00:10:26,709 --> 00:10:27,710
You'll think of something.

211
00:10:28,086 --> 00:10:30,380
And when we meet,
we can confirm our identities

212
00:10:30,463 --> 00:10:32,465
by showing our Shinigami to each other.

213
00:10:32,632 --> 00:10:34,342
-[L gasps]
-Shinigami?

214
00:10:34,634 --> 00:10:35,885
[Light] He's a liability.

215
00:10:35,969 --> 00:10:37,804
If I don't do something
about him quickly...

216
00:10:38,054 --> 00:10:39,806
-[L screams]
-What?

217
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:44,602
[L continues screaming and panting]

218
00:10:44,811 --> 00:10:45,979
[groans]

219
00:10:46,187 --> 00:10:47,188
Ryuzaki!

220
00:10:48,189 --> 00:10:50,024
-Are you all right?
-Shh...

221
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:52,360
Shinigami?

222
00:10:53,695 --> 00:10:55,363
Am I supposed to believe that?

223
00:10:55,488 --> 00:10:57,532
That Shinigami actually exist?

224
00:11:16,676 --> 00:11:18,428
Shi-- Shinigami?

225
00:11:19,721 --> 00:11:21,306
Am I supposed to believe that?

226
00:11:21,931 --> 00:11:24,309
That Shinigami actually exist?

227
00:11:24,684 --> 00:11:25,977
That's impossible...

228
00:11:26,477 --> 00:11:28,062
Obviously they don't exist.

229
00:11:28,646 --> 00:11:30,064
Yes, that's right, Ryuzaki.

230
00:11:30,190 --> 00:11:32,817
Listen to yourself.
Of course Shinigami don't exist.

231
00:11:33,193 --> 00:11:34,611
[nervous groan]

232
00:11:35,361 --> 00:11:37,864
You're probably right,
but I remember that Kira

233
00:11:37,947 --> 00:11:41,284
had those prisoners write something
suggesting the existence of Shinigami.

234
00:11:41,784 --> 00:11:43,286
So, based on that fact,

235
00:11:43,578 --> 00:11:46,122
perhaps we're dealing
with the same person after all.

236
00:11:46,372 --> 00:11:49,083
That would definitely explain
why we're hearing the same words.

237
00:11:49,209 --> 00:11:50,877
I don't think so, because...

238
00:11:51,252 --> 00:11:52,879
if this was the same person,

239
00:11:53,171 --> 00:11:56,758
it's highly unlikely he would have
responded to our video in the first place.

240
00:11:57,133 --> 00:11:59,010
[Light] And why would he agree
to let L live

241
00:11:59,093 --> 00:12:01,971
after going to all the trouble
of getting him to appear on TV?

242
00:12:02,096 --> 00:12:05,058
The real Kira wants him dead,
so it doesn't make sense.

243
00:12:05,183 --> 00:12:07,060
[Aizawa] Then maybe
there's some other connection

244
00:12:07,143 --> 00:12:08,895
between the real one and this new guy.

245
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:11,481
They could've already met
and decided to use the word "Shinigami"

246
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:12,774
as a way to confuse us.

247
00:12:12,899 --> 00:12:14,525
[L] No, I'd say that's unlikely.

248
00:12:14,609 --> 00:12:15,485
Hmm?

249
00:12:15,777 --> 00:12:16,945
[L] It's as Light says.

250
00:12:17,028 --> 00:12:18,613
If the two Kiras were connected,

251
00:12:18,696 --> 00:12:20,573
I don't think the impostor
would be so willing

252
00:12:20,657 --> 00:12:22,325
to give up on his plan to kill me.

253
00:12:23,076 --> 00:12:26,329
All of this suggests to me
that the copycat has his own agenda

254
00:12:26,412 --> 00:12:28,414
and is acting independently of the first.

255
00:12:29,332 --> 00:12:32,293
I believe his actual motivation
is to meet the original.

256
00:12:32,710 --> 00:12:34,003
I think you're right.

257
00:12:34,337 --> 00:12:36,464
He's acting out of an interest in Kira.

258
00:12:37,423 --> 00:12:41,469
The word "Shinigami" could very well be
some reference to their killing power.

259
00:12:42,262 --> 00:12:46,057
Saying we can confirm our identities
by showing our "Shinigami" to each other

260
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:48,393
probably means that they can confirm
their identities

261
00:12:48,476 --> 00:12:51,020
by somehow demonstrating
their ability to kill.

262
00:12:51,646 --> 00:12:52,939
Yes, that's it.

263
00:12:53,731 --> 00:12:55,024
[L] Based on their messages,

264
00:12:55,108 --> 00:12:58,444
we can assume that the word "Shinigami"
must hold some other meaning

265
00:12:58,528 --> 00:13:01,781
that only the real Kira
and the second Kira are aware of.

266
00:13:02,282 --> 00:13:05,660
Now, we just need to convince this copycat
to tell us what that is.

267
00:13:06,744 --> 00:13:09,372
[Light] So, will you respond
and force him to be more specific?

268
00:13:09,455 --> 00:13:11,207
We have to be careful how we handle this.

269
00:13:11,332 --> 00:13:13,334
We can't make it too obvious
that we're asking.

270
00:13:13,418 --> 00:13:15,795
Otherwise, he'll realize we're not Kira.

271
00:13:16,379 --> 00:13:20,633
[L] No, from now on, it's best
that we leave it up to the two Kiras.

272
00:13:20,758 --> 00:13:22,468
-Huh?
-What do you mean?

273
00:13:22,719 --> 00:13:24,637
[L] I imagine that the second Kira

274
00:13:24,721 --> 00:13:27,348
is probably quite satisfied
with the current situation,

275
00:13:27,432 --> 00:13:29,726
now that he's received
a televised response.

276
00:13:30,435 --> 00:13:32,895
He sent a message to get Kira's attention,

277
00:13:33,021 --> 00:13:35,023
and as far as he knows, he now has it.

278
00:13:35,398 --> 00:13:37,400
Also, there's that word he used,

279
00:13:37,483 --> 00:13:40,236
one that only the two of them
would understand.

280
00:13:40,403 --> 00:13:42,864
We'll arrange to have this reply
broadcast today

281
00:13:42,947 --> 00:13:44,574
on Sakura's six o'clock news.

282
00:13:44,657 --> 00:13:46,909
Naturally, this will be
of interest to Kira,

283
00:13:47,035 --> 00:13:49,746
and he'll be following this exchange
between the copycat

284
00:13:49,829 --> 00:13:51,122
and the one we have invented.

285
00:13:51,789 --> 00:13:54,792
Now, if I were Kira himself,
my priority would be

286
00:13:54,876 --> 00:13:58,171
to prevent this impostor from coming
into contact with the police.

287
00:13:58,504 --> 00:14:02,258
This is good for us, because it means
that the real Kira may feel pressured

288
00:14:02,342 --> 00:14:03,760
to respond this time.

289
00:14:04,302 --> 00:14:06,346
Okay. But let's say
that he doesn't respond.

290
00:14:06,429 --> 00:14:07,347
Then what do we do?

291
00:14:07,722 --> 00:14:10,892
[L] Yes, I've been thinking
about what the second Kira might do

292
00:14:10,975 --> 00:14:12,435
if he gets no response.

293
00:14:12,894 --> 00:14:17,023
For one, he might reveal more information
that he knows Kira wants kept secret.

294
00:14:17,231 --> 00:14:18,775
To pressure him into a meeting.

295
00:14:18,858 --> 00:14:21,235
Of course, that would make Kira nervous.

296
00:14:21,819 --> 00:14:23,696
It could be interesting.

297
00:14:24,113 --> 00:14:25,448
And what would be more interesting

298
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:29,202
is if Kira sends a message of his own
to prevent this from happening.

299
00:14:29,702 --> 00:14:31,287
Ideally, this could provide us

300
00:14:31,371 --> 00:14:34,082
with the physical evidence we'll need
to build a case against him.

301
00:14:34,916 --> 00:14:37,627
[L] In the meantime,
let's gather all the information we can

302
00:14:37,710 --> 00:14:38,961
on this copycat.

303
00:14:40,380 --> 00:14:42,256
[camera clicking]

304
00:14:43,883 --> 00:14:45,134
[photographer] Oh, that's good.

305
00:14:45,426 --> 00:14:47,178
Yes! Beautiful.

306
00:14:47,512 --> 00:14:49,097
Just like that. Perfect!

307
00:14:49,597 --> 00:14:51,849
I'm telling you,
these are gonna knock 'em dead.

308
00:14:52,475 --> 00:14:54,977
-You look like a little angel, Misa.
-[giggles]

309
00:14:55,228 --> 00:14:57,021
[Misa sighs] Oh, I'm so tired.

310
00:14:57,271 --> 00:14:58,856
That shoot went on forever.

311
00:14:58,940 --> 00:15:00,983
Modeling takes a lot of energy.

312
00:15:02,276 --> 00:15:03,403
[Misa] Hey, Rem.

313
00:15:03,569 --> 00:15:04,445
Huh?

314
00:15:04,612 --> 00:15:06,239
Can I ask you something?

315
00:15:06,531 --> 00:15:07,490
What is it?

316
00:15:07,990 --> 00:15:11,035
Each Shinigami has to have
one Death Note of their own.

317
00:15:11,202 --> 00:15:14,997
For a Shinigami to give a notebook
to a human, he needs to have two.

318
00:15:15,415 --> 00:15:19,335
Ryuk could give a Death Note to Kira,
because he somehow found a way

319
00:15:19,419 --> 00:15:21,754
to sneak an extra one
passed the Shinigami King.

320
00:15:22,338 --> 00:15:23,297
Right.

321
00:15:23,714 --> 00:15:24,924
What about you?

322
00:15:25,216 --> 00:15:28,344
The Shinigami King isn't someone
who is easily fooled.

323
00:15:28,511 --> 00:15:29,929
It doesn't happen often.

324
00:15:30,096 --> 00:15:31,722
Oh! Then how did I get mine?

325
00:15:32,557 --> 00:15:34,767
Let's just say it has
a lot to do with the fact

326
00:15:34,851 --> 00:15:37,270
that I'm one of the few
in the Shinigami Realm

327
00:15:37,353 --> 00:15:39,564
who knows how to kill another of my kind.

328
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:42,108
That's how I ended up with two.

329
00:15:42,567 --> 00:15:44,569
Oh, I think I get it.

330
00:15:44,861 --> 00:15:48,239
You killed a Shinigami and then
you gave his notebook to me, right?

331
00:15:48,656 --> 00:15:49,866
It's not like that.

332
00:15:50,074 --> 00:15:51,826
I wasn't the one who killed him.

333
00:15:52,118 --> 00:15:54,328
I just happened to be around when he died.

334
00:15:54,662 --> 00:15:56,497
It was coincidence, really.

335
00:15:57,373 --> 00:16:00,376
So, how do you kill a Shinigami?
I have to know.

336
00:16:01,461 --> 00:16:03,880
-Well?
-Never repeat this to anyone.

337
00:16:05,173 --> 00:16:07,884
I learned the only way
to kill a Shinigami...

338
00:16:09,218 --> 00:16:11,888
is to make them fall in love
with a human.

339
00:16:15,308 --> 00:16:17,393
What a beautiful way to kill.

340
00:16:22,773 --> 00:16:23,691
[bones creaking]

341
00:16:25,359 --> 00:16:28,070
[Rem] There once was
a Shinigami named Gelus,

342
00:16:28,196 --> 00:16:31,991
who spent all of his time
watching over a certain human girl.

343
00:16:32,533 --> 00:16:35,244
Gelus wanted nothing more
than to look at her

344
00:16:35,369 --> 00:16:37,538
as she went about her daily life.

345
00:16:48,299 --> 00:16:49,842
[Rem] It's today, isn't it?

346
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:51,344
Her last day alive?

347
00:16:52,220 --> 00:16:54,555
[Gelus] She looks so full of life.

348
00:16:55,473 --> 00:16:56,891
I wonder, why today?

349
00:16:57,558 --> 00:16:58,559
It's...

350
00:16:58,726 --> 00:17:00,978
[sniffs] It's just not fair.

351
00:17:06,234 --> 00:17:09,487
[Rem] I also wanted to find out
how she was going to die,

352
00:17:09,737 --> 00:17:11,656
so I stayed and watched with him.

353
00:17:15,409 --> 00:17:17,954
It was nighttime
and she was walking alone.

354
00:17:18,079 --> 00:17:19,580
No one else was around.

355
00:17:20,081 --> 00:17:21,541
And then it happened.

356
00:17:25,878 --> 00:17:28,589
A man suddenly appeared
and blocked her path.

357
00:17:28,798 --> 00:17:31,425
He was clearly infatuated with the girl.

358
00:17:31,634 --> 00:17:33,469
I love you more than anyone else
in the world!

359
00:17:33,719 --> 00:17:36,180
I'm always watching you!
I want to protect you forever!

360
00:17:36,347 --> 00:17:38,307
[Rem] She'd never seen the man before,

361
00:17:38,432 --> 00:17:40,601
and, of course, turned him down.

362
00:17:40,893 --> 00:17:41,978
[laughing manically]

363
00:17:43,020 --> 00:17:45,815
[sobbing]

364
00:17:46,232 --> 00:17:49,485
Then, if I can't have you...

365
00:17:50,653 --> 00:17:52,363
I'll kill us both!

366
00:17:52,697 --> 00:17:56,409
[screaming]

367
00:17:57,535 --> 00:17:58,703
Wait. Stop it!

368
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:00,204
What are you doing?

369
00:18:00,496 --> 00:18:02,373
[Gelus sobbing]

370
00:18:02,748 --> 00:18:07,128
Without even thinking, Gelus did something
that we Shinigami must never do.

371
00:18:07,587 --> 00:18:12,675
[man screaming and gasping for air]

372
00:18:12,925 --> 00:18:14,885
[choking]

373
00:18:22,727 --> 00:18:25,980
[Rem] Gelus used his Death Note
to kill the man instantly,

374
00:18:26,105 --> 00:18:28,190
and, therefore, saved the girl's life.

375
00:18:28,691 --> 00:18:30,568
It was the wrong thing to do.

376
00:18:30,901 --> 00:18:34,572
Shinigami exist only to shorten
and take human lives.

377
00:18:35,197 --> 00:18:38,868
We aren't permitted to undo
that which has been fated.

378
00:18:39,702 --> 00:18:46,584
[Gelus sobbing and groaning]

379
00:18:50,713 --> 00:18:52,298
[exhales]

380
00:18:55,593 --> 00:18:56,677
At that moment,

381
00:18:56,761 --> 00:19:00,097
Gelus became something
which was neither sand nor rust

382
00:19:00,181 --> 00:19:01,974
and disappeared forever.

383
00:19:02,475 --> 00:19:03,392
He died.

384
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:08,689
The only reminder of his existence
was his Death Note left behind.

385
00:19:11,359 --> 00:19:14,070
The rest of his lifespan
was added to hers.

386
00:19:14,403 --> 00:19:16,739
So, not only had he saved her life,

387
00:19:16,864 --> 00:19:20,451
he'd accidentally extended it
well beyond its natural end.

388
00:19:21,952 --> 00:19:24,330
So, if he'd never fallen in love
with this girl,

389
00:19:24,413 --> 00:19:26,874
he'd probably still be alive today,
wouldn't he?

390
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:28,334
That's right.

391
00:19:29,710 --> 00:19:30,586
Hmm...

392
00:19:32,254 --> 00:19:33,631
[Misa] I had no idea.

393
00:19:34,215 --> 00:19:35,841
All this time, I thought it was luck.

394
00:19:35,966 --> 00:19:38,719
But it was a Shinigami
who saved my life that day.

395
00:19:39,845 --> 00:19:40,721
Yes.

396
00:19:41,514 --> 00:19:43,933
Gelus loved you enough to die for you.

397
00:19:44,767 --> 00:19:47,895
So that Death Note is now yours to keep.

398
00:19:49,605 --> 00:19:50,481
Hmm.

399
00:19:54,402 --> 00:19:55,403
I see.

400
00:19:55,569 --> 00:19:58,447
For a Shinigami to die,
they have to love a human enough

401
00:19:58,531 --> 00:20:00,533
that they'd prevent their death
from happening.

402
00:20:00,908 --> 00:20:02,076
So, what about you, Rem?

403
00:20:02,284 --> 00:20:04,620
You're not in love with me, are you?
Be honest.

404
00:20:04,912 --> 00:20:06,038
Just forget it.

405
00:20:06,372 --> 00:20:08,791
You really think
you can kill me that easily?

406
00:20:09,291 --> 00:20:11,168
Oops. You saw through that?

407
00:20:11,502 --> 00:20:12,378
[giggles]

408
00:20:13,295 --> 00:20:14,463
I'm so glad.

409
00:20:14,547 --> 00:20:17,383
At least now I have something interesting
to tell Kira.

410
00:20:17,883 --> 00:20:18,968
But I wonder...

411
00:20:19,260 --> 00:20:24,056
Does he know how to K-I-L-L a Shinigami?

412
00:20:24,515 --> 00:20:27,518
I asked him on TV to find a way
for us to meet each other,

413
00:20:27,601 --> 00:20:29,103
but he hasn't replied to me yet.

414
00:20:29,395 --> 00:20:31,188
What's taking him so long?

415
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:33,524
Maybe I should just send him
another message.

416
00:20:37,820 --> 00:20:38,863
[Light] This isn't good.

417
00:20:38,988 --> 00:20:42,575
I can't allow this Second Kira
to act on his own for much longer.

418
00:20:42,742 --> 00:20:45,619
He's careless, so it's only
a matter of time before he slips up.

419
00:20:45,703 --> 00:20:47,830
And when he does,
the police will be waiting.

420
00:20:47,997 --> 00:20:51,083
With him in custody, they could find out
about the Death Note.

421
00:20:53,878 --> 00:20:55,004
[waiter] Something to start?

422
00:20:55,296 --> 00:20:57,923
[Misa] Hmm, a strawberry sundae, please.

423
00:20:58,340 --> 00:20:59,717
Of course. Be right back.

424
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:02,928
[sighs] What should I do?

425
00:21:03,220 --> 00:21:06,807
How can I contact the Second Kira
without L noticing anything?

426
00:21:08,184 --> 00:21:10,436
-Here you go. Enjoy.
-Mmm!

427
00:21:14,231 --> 00:21:16,358
I can't wait to meet Kira!

428
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:18,277
I wonder...

429
00:21:18,402 --> 00:21:21,155
What kind of person are you, impostor?

430
00:21:21,989 --> 00:21:22,907
I wonder...

431
00:21:22,990 --> 00:21:25,201
What kind of person are you, Kira?

432
00:21:25,326 --> 00:21:26,368
Mmm. [giggles]

433
00:21:30,456 --> 00:21:36,462
TO BE CONTINUED

434
00:21:41,801 --> 00:21:43,594
[theme music playing]
